PassportElementErrorSelfie#

class masogram.types.passport_element_error_selfie.PassportElementErrorSelfie(*, source: str = 'selfie', type: str, file_hash: str, message: str, **extra_data: Any)[source]#

Represents an issue with the selfie with a document. The error is considered resolved when the file with the selfie changes.

Source: https://core.telegram.org/bots/api#passportelementerrorselfie

source: str#

Error source, must be selfie

type: str#

The section of the user’s Telegram Passport which has the issue, one of ‘passport’, ‘driver_license’, ‘identity_card’, ‘internal_passport’

file_hash: str#

Base64-encoded hash of the file with the selfie

message: str#

Error message
